OL,3,CDramatic decline in insect populations
OL,4,Cover last 50 years, study finds
OL,6,FThe survey is conducted on Applesham
OL,7,FFarm near Lancing in Sussex by the
OL,8,FHampshire-based Game and Wildlife
OL,9,FConservation Trust and is the world's
OL,10,Flongest-running study of its kind.
OL,12,FResearchers say that the decline in
OL,13,Finsect populations can have an impact
OL,14,Fon many species of farmland birds like
OL,15,FGrey Partridges, Skylarks and Turtle
OL,16,FDoves.
OL,18,FIntensive agriculture, pesticide use
OL,19,Fand climate change are all thought to
OL,20,Fbe factors.
