OL,3,CDramatic decline in insect populations
OL,4,Cover last 50 years, study finds
OL,6,FApplesham Farm near Lancing has been
OL,7,Frun by the same family for five
OL,8,Fgenerations, covering 1,000 acres.
OL,10,FIt is a traditional mixed farm, using
OL,11,Fno pesticides in the summer, and is
OL,12,Ftrying to be as wildlife-friendly as
OL,13,Fpossible.
OL,15,FFarmer Hugh Passmore said: "We under-
OL,16,Fsow Spring barley - so when we plant
OL,17,Fthe barley we're also planting grass -
OL,18,Fand that benefits insect life greatly.
OL,19,FWe've got chalk grass here which a
OL,20,Fhome for a lot of insect life and they
OL,21,Fcan then spread into the fields."
